## Guidelines

Work surgically: understand the existing code before changing it, keep the smallest change that satisfies the request, and do not refactor unrelated code. State unclear assumptions instead of guessing.

Before editing, define the success check for the task. For bug fixes, reproduce or cover the bug first when practical. For feature work, update only the files needed for the accepted scope.

Use the repository's existing commands, style, and test layout. Do not commit secrets, generated runtime data, or unrelated local changes.

## Asset Bundles

Bundled agent assets live in `.asset-bundles`. The `.claude` and `.agents` entries may be symlinks to that directory; keep that structure and do not duplicate bundle files elsewhere.

Use these global bundles when present:

- `feature-implementieren` (`.asset-bundles/skills/feature-implementieren/SKILL.md`): use for requests to implement a feature from `docs/features/00-feature-set-overview.md`, including `$feature-implementieren`.
- `global.living-sync-reporter` (`.asset-bundles/skills/global.living-sync-reporter/living-sync-reporter/SKILL.md`): use for Living Sync progress, test, code-change, blocker, note, and completion reports. Prefer the bundled reporter binary over hand-written curl calls.

## Verification

Run the narrowest relevant checks first, then broaden when the change touches shared behavior. Report exactly what passed or failed. If a full check fails because of unrelated existing issues, name the failing files and still verify your changed files.

Keep final responses short: summarize the change, list verification, and call out any remaining risk or unrelated dirty worktree state.
